[{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"The API reference below is generated from docstrings in the source code.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Index","page":"API Reference","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Docstrings","page":"API Reference","title":"Docstrings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#MyPkg52.hello-Tuple{}","page":"API Reference","title":"MyPkg52.hello","text":"hello() -> String\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"developer/#Developer-Guide","page":"Developer Guide","title":"Developer Guide","text":"If you are planning significant changes, open an issue first. The ColPrac guidelines are recommended.","category":"section"},{"location":"developer/#One-Time-Local-Setup","page":"Developer Guide","title":"One-Time Local Setup","text":"Clone the repository and install development tools, Revise.jl and Runic.jl.\n\n# Clone the repository\ngit clone https://github.com/ohno/MyPkg52.jl.git\ncd MyPkg52.jl\n\n# Install tools\njulia --startup-file=no -e 'import Pkg; Pkg.add(\"Revise\")'\njulia --project=@runic --startup-file=no -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.add(\"Runic\")'\n\n# Instantiate dependencies\njulia --project=. --startup-file=no -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.instantiate()'","category":"section"},{"location":"developer/#Daily-Development-Flow","page":"Developer Guide","title":"Daily Development Flow","text":"This section describes the typical workflow for making changes to the package.\n\nStart an interactive session with Revise.jl.\ncd MyPkg52.jl\njulia --startup-file=no -i -E 'using Revise; import Pkg; Pkg.activate(\".\"); using MyPkg52'\nChange the source code.\nFormat the source code with Runic.jl.\nRun the tests.\nBuild the documentation locally.\nSubmit a pull request (after steps 3â€“5 succeed).\n\n# Start\ncd MyPkg52.jl\njulia --startup-file=no -i -E 'using Revise; import Pkg; Pkg.activate(\".\"); using MyPkg52'\n\n# Format\njulia --project=@runic --startup-file=no -e 'using Runic; exit(Runic.main(ARGS))' -- --inplace .\n\n# Run test\njulia --project=. --startup-file=no -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.test()'\n\n# Generate documentation\njulia --project=docs --startup-file=no -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.develop(PackageSpec(path=pwd())); Pkg.instantiate();'\njulia --project=docs --startup-file=no -e 'include(\"docs/make.jl\")'\n\nTo change the source code:\n\nWhen making new functions or updating docstrings, refer to Documenter: Adding docstrings.\nIf you need a new dependency, use julia --project=. --startup-file=no -e 'import Pkg; Pkg.add(\"SomePackage\"); Pkg.resolve(); Pkg.instantiate()'. Replace SomePackage with the actual package name.\n\nFor Julia package development basics, see:\n\nHow to develop a Julia package\nPkg: Creating packages","category":"section"},{"location":"developer/#Versioning-and-Registering-(for-Maintainers)","page":"Developer Guide","title":"Versioning and Registering (for Maintainers)","text":"This project follows Semantic Versioning. When bumping the version, update the version number in:\n\nProject.toml\nCITATION.bib\n\nTo register this package in the General registry, install Registrator and use via the GitHub App.","category":"section"},{"location":"user/#User-Guide","page":"User Guide","title":"User Guide","text":"Before starting the tutorial, complete the Installation and Quick Start sections.","category":"section"},{"location":"user/#Tutorial","page":"User Guide","title":"Tutorial","text":"import MyPkg52\nMyPkg52.hello()","category":"section"},{"location":"user/#Examples","page":"User Guide","title":"Examples","text":"import MyPkg52\ntext_1 = MyPkg52.hello()\ntext_2 = \"Goodbye, World!\"\ntext_1 * \" \" * text_2","category":"section"},{"location":"#MyPkg52.jl","page":"Home","title":"MyPkg52.jl","text":"(Image: Stable) (Image: Dev) (Image: License) (Image: Build Status) (Image: Coverage) (Image: Aqua QA) (Image: JET Test) (Image: code style: runic) (Image: ColPrac: Contributor's Guide on Collaborative Practices for Community Packages)\n\nA Julia package for solving my problems.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"Run the following command in the Julia REPL (or in a notebook):\n\njulia> import Pkg; Pkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/ohno/MyPkg52.jl.git\")","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","title":"Quick Start","text":"After installation, run the following example to load the package and verify that it works:\n\nimport MyPkg52; MyPkg52.hello()","category":"section"},{"location":"#User-Guide","page":"Home","title":"User Guide","text":"For detailed usage instructions and examples, see the User Guide.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Developer-Guide","page":"Home","title":"Developer Guide","text":"For contribution and maintenance workflows, see the Developer Guide.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Support","page":"Home","title":"Support","text":"Feature requests and bug reports are handled through GitHub Issues.","category":"section"},{"location":"#API-Reference","page":"Home","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Citation","page":"Home","title":"Citation","text":"CITATION.bib is available for citing this package.\n\nfile = open(\"../../CITATION.bib\", \"r\") # hide\ntext = Base.read(file, String) # hide\nclose(file) # hide\nprintln(text) # hide","category":"section"},{"location":"#License","page":"Home","title":"License","text":"This package is released under the MIT License.\n\nfile = open(\"../../LICENSE\", \"r\") # hide\ntext = Base.read(file, String) # hide\nclose(file) # hide\nprintln(text) # hide","category":"section"},{"location":"#Acknowledgment","page":"Home","title":"Acknowledgment","text":"This package is written in the Julia programming language, built on an initial project template generated using PkgStarter.jl. This repository is hosted on GitHub, and continuous integration is run using GitHub Actions.","category":"section"}]
